The following consumers are connected:
2 instrument-panel lamps (Schaltbrettleuchten), 1 bulb each — 3 W; operated by a separate switch;
1 indicator lamp (Anzeigeleuchte) in the switch box, 1 bulb — 3 W, for the dynamo; operated by the switch key in the switch box (Schaltkasten);
1 night-march set (Nachtmarschgerät): 1 blackout headlamp (Tarnscheinwerfer) — 35 W and 1 convoy-spacing tail-light (Abstandrücklicht) — 10 W;
1 electric starter, operated via a push-button on the instrument panel through an electromagnetic battery switch (Batterieschalter);
1 electric priming fuel pump, operated by a push-button on the instrument panel;
1 superstructure lighting set (Aufbau-Lichter).
Furthermore, the following can be connected via two sockets (Steckdosen) on the instrument panel:
1. one magnetic lamp (Magnetlampe) with a 6 m lead, 1 bulb — 15 W;
2. the fighting-compartment lighting (Kampfraumbeleuchtung);
3. the gun firing trigger (Geschützabzug) with two indicator lamps — 3 W each.
The radio set (Funkanlage) is connected via a junction box (Abzweigdose) on the left side wall of the fighting compartment.
The electrical system is fitted with:
12 fuse cartridges (Sicherungspatronen) of 15 A in three fuse boxes (Sicherungsdosen);
1 fuse cartridge of 60 A in the regulator switch.
Besides a dynamo and a starter, the engine is fitted with an impulse magneto (Schnappermagnetzünder).
The electrical system includes a switch box (Schaltkasten) housed in the instrument panel; an indicator lamp and a dip lever (Abblendhebel) are built into it.
The switch box has three positions (0, 1, 2); the key can be withdrawn in each of the three positions.
Correct operation of the dynamo is shown by the charge-indicator lamp (Ladeanzeigeleuchte) in the switch box going out when the engine is running.
To allow interference-free wireless reception, the vehicle's electrical equipment is suppressed to interference-suppression class Ia (Entstörklasse Ia).

