1 fuel-contents gauge (Kraftstoffvorratszeiger) with a pull-knob for its air pump;
1 lever for operating the fuel shut-off cock;
1 lever for operating the bottom valve under the fuel tank;
1 handle for adjusting the flaps in front of the air-inlet openings in the rear armour.
In the engine compartment, on the left side of the hull:
2 interference suppressors (Entstörer) for the dynamo;
1 electric priming fuel pump.
15. Werkzeug  -  15. Tools
For minor repair work, tools and spare parts are carried inside or on the vehicle in two boxes.
Box 1 (in the chassis floor, left) contains the tools and spare parts needed for repairing the track.
Box 2 (on the engine deck) contains tools and some spare parts for the vehicle and the engine.
In addition, besides some small accessories, the following are carried:
inside the chassis, to the left of the driver's seat: 4 socket spanners (Steckschlüssel) for adjusting the brakes;
on the clutch box: 2 spanners for the belt tensioner of the fan drive;
to the right of the driver's seat: 2 spanners for the track connector (Kettenschließer).

Original page 31
16. Hilfsgerät  -  16. Auxiliary equipment
On the track guards (Kettenabdeckungen) or at the rear:
1 jack (Wagenwinde) of 10-tonne capacity;
1 chock (Unterlegklotz);
1 track tensioner (Kettenspanner);
1 crowbar (Brechstange);
1 fire extinguisher (Feuerlöscher);
2 tow ropes (Abschleppseile), 5 m long, for 10-tonne pull;
2 S-hooks (S-Haken);
1 hand crank (Andrehkurbel);
1 large wire cutter (Drahtschere).
In the fighting compartment: 1 fire extinguisher.
17. Schanzzeug  -  17. Entrenching tools
The following entrenching tools are stowed on the track guards:
1 long spade (Spaten);
1 medium-length axe (Axt).
